Package org.opensextant.giscore.output.rss

Class GeoRSSOutputStream

java.lang.Object
org.opensextant.giscore.output.StreamVisitorBase
org.opensextant.giscore.output.XmlOutputStreamBase
org.opensextant.giscore.output.rss.GeoRSSOutputStream
All Implemented Interfaces:
Closeable, AutoCloseable, IStreamVisitor, IGISOutputStream, IRss
public class GeoRSSOutputStream extends XmlOutputStreamBase implements IRss
The GeoRSS output stream creates a RSS 2.0 document with GeoRSS-Simple locations using the given output stream. It uses STaX methods for writing the XML elements to avoid building an in-memory DOM, which reduces the memory overhead of creating the document.

GeoRSSOutputStream produces a valid GeoRSS XML document wrt the RSS 2.0 specification and GeoRSS-Simple encodings.

Notes/Limitations:

-Handles all basic GeoRSS-simple shapes (Point, Line, Polygon, Circle).
-Current georss-Simple spec, however, does not have a native collection/multigeometry feature (though one is proposed) so for now the more complex geometries (MultiPoint, MultiLine, MultiLinearRings, MultiPolygons) simply output the first geometry in the group. Proposed fix would be to output gml features for those shapes.
-GeoRSS-Simple doesn't really have a one-to-one mapping for a LinearRing so using a georss:line for now.

Jason Mathews, MITRE Corp. Date: Jun 6, 2009 5:50:46 PM

      Creates a GeoRSSOutputStream that uses the specified underlying OutputStream.
      Parameters:
      stream - the underlying output stream.
      encoding - the encoding to use
      namespaceMap - Mapping of non-RSS element names (can appear in channel properties as passed in the channelMap argument or in items as extended data) to explicit namespaces. Extended data properties in Features are checked against this mapping. If no mapping exists for a given property name then it is assumed to be part of the RssChannel or RssItem definition otherwise the RSS may not be valid.
      channelMap - simple child elements that are added to the channel element (e.g. title, link, category, etc. or user-defined ones if namespace mapping is provided). Note that the title, link, and description are considered require elements for the channel. See ...
      Throws:
      XMLStreamException - if there is an error with the underlying XML
